:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="134" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[181,1142,832,1411]" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">
Oldroyd probably did not examine the types of 
<taxonomicName box="[832,932,1353,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Anypodetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[832,932,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Oldroyd, 1974" authorityName=": Oldroyd" authorityYear="1974" box="[945,1049,1352,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Anypodetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rigidis">
<emphasis box="[945,1049,1352,1379]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">A. rigidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName box="[462,562,1385,1411]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Anypodetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis box="[462,562,1385,1411]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and so I have synonymised 
<taxonomicName authority="Oldroyd, 1974" authorityName=": Oldroyd" authorityYear="1974" box="[879,952,1384,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Anypodetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rigidis">
<emphasis box="[879,952,1384,1410]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">rigidis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
